                <h1>Judaism: The World's Oldest Monotheistic Religion</h1>
                <p>Judaism is one of the oldest monotheistic religions, with roots tracing back over 3,000 years. It originated in the ancient Near East with the covenant between God and the patriarch Abraham. Throughout history, Judaism has evolved, influencing various cultures and maintaining its core beliefs and practices to this day.</p>
